                <td bgcolor="#3C4884" valign="top"><font color="white" face="verdana" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;03/19/2004&nbsp;: 2:10:55 PM</small><hr size="1"><span class="spnMessageText"> two things I will chime in with. if this has been repeated I dont care. im two lazy to read everything.<br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="1" face="verdana" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote">Dont bother FD pulling these, if snare resists keep running and recasting until it lands. If snare fails on pull and you FD these mobs warp nearly everytime - so dont bother.<br /><hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></font id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"><br /><br />99.9% of all warps in PoF are caused by one thing. you go to dark a mob and the mob resists, you casted from max range so you didnt find it nessasary to move back a bit prior to FD. the mob resets and you stand up, still not moved from the original spot...you cast dark again...and boom warp. everytime. the moral of the story is this. if you cast from one spot and then fd in that same spot, you need to move a bit before you cast snare again, otherwise you get a warp.<br /><br />one more tip i will add here. If you pull with dark, follow it up with a splurt. the nice thing about splurt is you always know based on the damage when its about to finish. so when you see "your splurt has wore off..." you know you have 3-4 tries to resnare before your dark goes. <br /></span></font></td>
