                <td bgcolor="#3C4884" valign="top"><font color="white" face="verdana" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;03/05/2004&nbsp;: 04:23:48 AM</small><hr size="1"><span class="spnMessageText"> Tables often overcamped on my server, if so I often use another good Pofire XP camp.<br /><br />Many of you probably know or it - but some may not. It's not as good as tables in terms of raw xp per kill but must be the next best solo XP spot in the game and these mobs die faster. Netting 9% AA per kill approx. The camp is where you set up to kill the two cheap birds, pulling the doomfire guys from Fort 1 and kiting them up and down past the bridge with magma guys. On the map the spot is to the left of the northmost Fort wall and the word 'UP' on the NW of map. Basically pull everything from fort - unending supply of mobs all soloable. Dont bother FD pulling these, if snare resists keep running and recasting until it lands. If snare fails on pull and you FD these mobs warp nearly everytime - so dont bother.<br /><br />Be warned these are more resistant to snare than the table mobs (worst case was 12 resists in a row). If the snare resists really freak you out, you can actually land scent of terris on these (usually in 2-3 casts) and then resist is virtually nil, but lowers your dps form lost spell slot and time to land terris - but 12 snare resists really sucks!. I use usual spell set here but substitue Splurt for FP and CoC (yes it lands here) for Pyro (Neuro just does not land enough and I dont have Horror but suspect would resist also). Avoid chaplins, they are clerics and like to CH themselves. I like this camp as it always open, it's actually more interesting than tables, unending supply of mobs to kill.<br /><br />Edit: Changed word 'castle' to 'fort' to avoid confussion<br /></span></font></td>
