              <tr>
                <td bgcolor="#37437B" valign="top"
 nowrap><b><font color="white" face="verdana" size="2">Eldaabo Locomuerte</font></b></td>
                <td bgcolor="#37437B" valign="top"><font color="white" face="verdana" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;01/15/2004&nbsp;: 7:07:37 PM</small><hr size="1"><span class="spnMessageText"> I've spent a lot of time gathering AAs here.  I have AEIV, AHIV, BAIV, FT12, couple regen.  Here are some of my observations.<br /><br />Solo:<br /><br />63 SK pet with LDON augment hasted with Rune of Death<br />Pull with embracing darkness.<br />Load Dark Plague, BoT, send pet, splurt.<br />Refresh Bot when it wears...total of four times<br />Re-darkness at ~ 65%<br />Refresh Splurt and DP ~ 50% when they wear off.<br />Re-darkness at ~ 35%<br />Apply Saryn's Kiss when necessary, one per mob.<br />In total, 4 BoT, 2 DP, 2 Splurt, 1 SK and constant ED<br /><br />Doing this, I can kill the 9 in the tables area and one from inside before respawns.  Always try to sit as often as possible.  I re-apply ED early, as sometimes they can resist numerous casts.<br /><br />In general, if I'm going to be there a while, I'll stick with this lineup.  Its the most efficient I've been able to achieve.  If I know I'm going to be logging soon, I'll start throwing on Horror to speed kills up a bit, but the mana stats to slowly deplete.<br /><br />The gear and focuses I have make things more efficient.  I would say Affliction Haste is the most important, for safety's sake.  After a string of ED resists, you'll appreciate the 2.1 cast time.  Otherwise, you'll most likely have to FD (after FD-ing pet, if possible) and try to start again with some room.  I couldn't figure out a way to get ED off un-hasted when snare broke.  I recently picked up AEIV, and have been toying with how it affects my kill rate.  I've been mostly grouping lately, or burning mana at the end of the night anyway, so its hard to tell what effect it has on long-term kiting, but I think it would prolly let me get a Horror in per mob, without too much hurt on the mana.  Which in turn might get another mob into the cycle.<br /><br />Grouping:<br /><br />In general, I'll round up a bunch of guildies to group here.  The key I have found is to have two toons that can kite.  Usually, its me and another necro, one will be kiting, the other will just sic the pet, maybe apply a SK or horror, then go grab a new one.  This way there is always one in camp, and the aggro you can generate while waiting for the first to die means no chance of other people out-aggroing you.  I've found that if I'm the only kiter in a group, and I have to go grab mobs after the first is killed, that it takes a lot of time, especially after you start running to the front of the castle to clear the PHs.<br /><br />The other setup I found works is to have an enchanter to work the pulls.  While the group is killing the one you are kiting, the enchanter goes, pulls one with tash, brings it to the tables, and mezzes it.  When the mob you are kiting dies, just break mez with ED, pop a BoT on, and you should have sufficient aggro for the chanter to run and grab another.  Depending on the group, I'll throw a Horror and/or CoC on for extra aggro and damage.  Having a chanter also makes the chain-CHing clerics much easier to kill.  A well timed chanter-mez and a concentrated effort by the nukers can kill the cleric before it gets a CH off.  I don't think I've ever seen a cleric get inturrupted any other way.  If there's no chanter, you have to grind it out til the cleric runs oom, or hope to get a good string of crits from the nukers.<br /><br />One night, with chanter pulling, me kiting, 2 wizzies, 1 druid, 1 mage, we were averaging about 25 minute AAs.  (Helped that we also had an out of group bard singing mana)  To kite, I would ED, BoT and Horror, and the mobs would die maybe a tick after BoT and Horror wore off.  Was killer.<br /><br />The other nice thing about grouping here, is the possibility of getting a named to spawn from the castle.  I've gotten a nice 85/85, regen 2 ring off the named.  The named summon, but the one we killed was a caster, and we basically burned it down while it cast crappy nukes, summon kiting with whoever had aggro.  Helped to have the chanter slow.  Lets see if I can get the links right....<br /><br /><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=20804" target="_blank"><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=20804" target="_blank">http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=20804</a></a><br /><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=18959" target="_blank"><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=18959" target="_blank">http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=18959</a></a><br /><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=20803" target="_blank"><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=20803" target="_blank">http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=20803</a></a><br /><br />The named will spawn in the huts in the castle.  As far as I can tell, the huts usualy have 4 mobs in them, one in each corner of the room.  If the hut has a fifth mob in the center, that should be a PH for the named.  Named are rare, I'd say a 1/25, maybe even 1/50 spawn from the PHs.  With a full group with good DPS, you should be able to keep the three huts with PHs cleared.<br /><br />Usually, I'll end up with a mish-mash group, and we won't get exp quite as fast as soloing, but the fact that you have people to chat with and the capability of taking breaks and getting resses or whatever offsets the loss for me.  The added AAs in the guild for clerics or warriors or whatever non-DPS class in the group seems like a reasonable trade off for slightly slower AA dings.<br /><br />Anyone care to comment, or add more observations?<br /><br />Eldaabo Locomuerte<br />Dawntreaders<br />Terris Thule</span></font></td>
