 nowrap><b><font color="white" face="verdana" size="2">Wudiskar</font></b></td>
                <td bgcolor="#3C4884" valign="top"><font color="white" face="verdana" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;01/13/2004&nbsp;: 12:47:58 PM</small><hr size="1"><span class="spnMessageText"> 1- a Doomfire mob in PoFire is 14% AAXP, nothing less nothing more, not 16% as 1st poster claims<br /><br />- Got all excited, thought it was 16 percent, it USED to be 16 percent then, they had nerfed it some a while back.<br /><br />2- Doing it his way will probably enable you to go 30mn/AA, but you won't last more than 1 or 2 AAs (well tables are so boring you may not want to stay there for too long, that's true) because you'll completely blow your mana<br /><br />- This is totally dependent on your gear, mana, mana regen, aa's, and 'playstyle'. One thing I absolutely LOVE about necro's and laying on the dots is all of the 'stuff' that's going down in the background while those dots are ticking.. how much dmg per tic, how much mana used, mana regen rate, wtd refresh, rebuff my pet, which dot is going to wear off (I sometimes start recasting a dot before I get the 'wears off' message, and I'll get the wears off message before I finish casting). <br /><br />-Other 'brain ticking' moves, for example, if I get 3 dark resists in a row, I'll try Horror once, and if it's resisted, I may or may not skip recasting it again, b/c I am pretty sure it'll probably get resisted. If I see that I used up x ammount of mana on that pull, I may sit, stretch, send a tell or two and rest a second before resuming pulls. After over 100 aa dings at the picnic tables, I'd say I can give some 'tested and tried' advice on what works for me there.<br /><br />-Another point to make, is that I've found it way less stressfull to burn up that mana, kill the mob in less than 4 minutes, then sit and med for a few seconds, and resume pulls. "4 minutes, short rest, 4 minutes, short rest, repeat" &gt; "5 minute kills, nonstop pulling, conserving mana." <br /><br />-AND if I solo a mob in less than 4 minutes, I only need 2 Embracing Darkness casts (save little mana), and usually only cast 1 Saryn's Kiss and 1 Dark Plague. I let Horror and BoT do most of the work. If you are 'stretching' things out, you might be casting Saryn's Kiss x2, DPx2, EDx3?...<br /><br />-Again, when I started exp'ing here at picnic tables, it took me a good 45 minutes to solo an aa, but through the course of 100 aa's, a few equipment upgrades, INTENSE waiting till the last second to stand up, and run again, I feel I've about maximized my aa potential here, with my current setup of aa's and mana regen (I'm currently working on the extended affliction aug in BB to go further).<br /><br />Don't chain Horror for example, it's quite efficient in itself (more than BoT anyway), but resisted often and the mana/tick you need to sustain it is very high, use it only when you have too much mana (above 90-95%) to haste a kill<br /><br />-I used to agree with this. I got SOO frustrated with horror resists at times, that I'd unmem it. BUT, I 'tried again' and now, for some reason, I seem to get a lot less resists overall (over the last 30 or so aa's that is)<br /><br />-While I'm at it, and b/c this is a guide section, I'll share a couple other 'tricks'. If you plan on being able to crank out a LONG exp session here, pick up a journeyman's walking stick for your pet. The debuff will do wonders for your dots :)<br /><br />-This should be a no brainer BUT, if you don't have a burning affliction, or equivalent focus item (and a affliction effeciency 4), DON'T COME HERE UNTIL YOU GET STUFF FROM A MAGE!<br /><br />-GROUP UP HERE! There are a couple variations on this. Multiple necro's, each kiting their own mob individually works well, or 'any combo' all focus'ing on one kited mob. I like the 'whole group on one mob' personally (especially when there are 2 necro's in group), b/c mobs go down real fast, you pull nonstop, and can pull any kind of mob (clerics go down fast too). AND you can rotate out taking breaks, to keep group from all burning out from the fast paced killing (I've even rotated out 'timed' 5 minute breaks before). The only thing that really sucks about the full group thing is if you get people in the group who don't do their share. For me though, I really dont care too much, b/c guildies getting aa's makes my guild more powerfull and helps me in long run too (often have a cleric in my group heh)<br /><br />I RARELY find grouping better exp than solo'ing though! HOWEVER, I can sit here grouped for hours, chatting, taking turns doing the kiting, taking my afk breaks, and seeing the aa's go by w/o coming close to 'burning out' b/c I get bored or too stressed at the spot.</span></font></td>
              </tr>
